items.description:
This is my first attempt at a lora ever, so I don't really know what I'm doing. However, I noticed despite many of the genshin characters having a lora, there is not one for Aether, the main character of the game! üò® So I made one, good or not I felt the obligation to share bc who doesn't love Aether

Use "aether \(genshin impact\)" in your prompt (and probably 1boy, solo)

To get the normal clothes, use some of the following "cape, earrings, jewelry, gloves, midriff, navel, scarf, braid, single braid, etc."

The other aspects like the hair and eyes were pruned but also might not show up because they were pruned so yeah. Tends to prefer unshotafying him which can be a pro or con depending on who you are.

Trained using the base AOM3 model, works with other things.

Update: I was gonna make a better version/ normal Lora version but no matter what I did the results were worse than when I had no idea what I was doing so... enjoy?

items.description:
Character from Dracu-Riot! by Yuzusoft.

Training settings:

20 Epochs (this version is 14th epoch checkpoint), 20 steps, fp16, Lr=1e-4, cosine scheduler, 10% warm up, AdamW, CLIP skip 2

For using this LoRA, please refer the sample grid for CFG and LoRA weight.

For simplicity, use CFG scale within 4-6 and LoRA weight around 0.9.

This LoRA is trained on https://civitai.com/models/17394/quinns-colorfulmix

Sample prompt used for all samples (may have small adjustment):

<lora:Elena_v4_2:0.9>, Elena_Owen, masterpiece, (masterpiece, best quality), a girl, solo, (mature female:1.2), HDR, Ray Tracing, glistering shiny, best colors, bloom, (depth of field), (looking at viewer, smirk), (low_angle), beautiful face, beautiful eyes, ((silver hair, thick hair, black ribbon)), (black panties, pantyhose, cameltoe), (topless), (glasses), parted lips, boobs, (beautiful eyes, light blue iris), squatting, pussy, (inside, windows open, office, sun ray, sunlight, framed paint)

easynegative

CFG:4, DPM++ 2M Karras, 20 steps, R-ESRGAN 4x+ Anime6B upscaler, 0.45 denoising strength, 512*512 generation size and upcaled by 2. Finally using R-ESRGAN 4x+ Anime6B to upscale again for 2k image.

This LoRA has been trained using the Anything v4.5 model. It does a great job at generating characters that look almost exactly like Meer Campbell from the Mobile Suit Gundam SEED (Destiny) series. She usually wears her idol outfit when generating with this LoRA so it might be hard to put her into different clothes this time. If you are Using A1111's Webui you want to move the file into the models>Lora directory. It is very important to use the relevant trigger word so that you can get results that look close to mine or even better.

  • Copy the file to stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora

  • Select your LoRA like in this video

  • Make sure to change the weight (by default it's :1 which is usually too high)

Although a lot of work has been spent on the follow-up, the first version is still the one that can barely be called usable, and since it has received some good comments, I still intend to release it for everyone to try.
